All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
App
Default entry point class
ApplicationWindow
This class is responsible for initializing and display the primary stage of the graphical interface.
AssetLoader
This class is responsible for loading the tile templates, game maps, and images
Cart
Represents a cart.
CartState
An enum representing the various state a cart can be in
FXCart
Represents a graphical wrapper for a cart.
FXTower
Represents a graphical wrapper for a tower.
FXWrappers
This class is responsible for handling creation, storing and deletion of fx wrappers for towers and carts
GameController
This class is responsible for controlling and managing sub-controllers for the graphical game interface.
GameDifficulty
An enum representing the difficulty of the game Each difficulty has a set of parameters that affect the game play, such as the starting money, the number of carts, and the money earn multiplier.
GameEnvironment
The overarching, main class of the game This class is a Singleton; use .getGameEnvironment() to get the instance of this class and all its subcomponents;
GameMap
This class represents a map in the game.
GameRound
Represents a single round in the game Each round has a number, a list of cart and a set of actions to be preformed at the end of the round
GameRoundFactory
This class is responsible for creating instances of the GameRound class It uses the games difficulty and round number to determine the number of carts and velocities
GameState
An enum representing the various states the game can be in.
GameStateHandler
This class manages the game state within the game environment.
InventoryController
This class is a sub-controller of the GameController and is responsible for handling events related the inventory
Item
Represents an instance of an Item (a Tower or UpgradeItem).
MainController
This class is responsible for controlling the main menu graphical interface.
MapInteraction
Enumerations the types of map interactions that can occur on the game map
MapInteractionController
This class is a sub-controller of the GameController and is responsible for handling map interactions
NameValidatorService
This service validates a given name
PathFinderService
This service finds and validates a path in the map given a matrix
PathFinderServiceTest
 
Purchasable
Represents an item that is purchasable from the shop.
RandomEvent
Represents the contract for random events in the game.
RandomEventBrokenTower
Represents a random event where a tower becomes broken
RandomEvents
Represents a collection of random events within the game
RandomEventTowerStatsDecrease
Represents a random event where a tower has its stats decreased
RandomEventTowerStatsIncrease
Represents a random event where a tower has its stats increased
ResourceType
Enum representing the types of resources
Shop
This class represents the shop.
ShopController
This class is a sub-controller of the GameController and is responsible for handing events in the shop
Tile
Represents a tile on the game map which stores properties relating to build-ability, location and if it is a path tile
TileNotFoundException
Unchecked exception that indicates a tile was not found
TileTemplate
This class represents a template for a tile on a map.
Tower
Represents a tower in the game.
Tower.Type
This interface represents the types of towers
TowerType
Represents a type of tower.
Upgradeable
Represents an object that can be upgraded
UpgradeItem
Represents an upgrade item that can be purchased and applied to a tower or cart
UpgradeItem.Type
This interface represents the types of Upgrade Items
UpgradeItemFasterReload
Represents the faster reload tower upgrade
UpgradeItemFillCart
Represents the fill cart upgrade
UpgradeItemRepairTower
Represents the repair tower upgrade
UpgradeItemSlowerCart
Represents the slower cart upgrade
WindowManager
This class is responsible for managing the different screens within the game.
